        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 10:32AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1032 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pittsboro, or 22 miles southeast of Water Valley, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsboro, Slate Springs, Thorn, Egypt, Reid, Sabougla, Loyd, Pyland,
Ellard, Vardaman, Woodland, Thelma, McCondy, Atlanta, Retreat,
Okolona, Leotis, Dentontown, Buena Vista, and Sparta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
